<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-23T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-23T09:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6836:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-23T16:00:00+02:00">November 23, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received November 23—3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>4815. The German press after having in the recent past given a
                                    good deal of space to comment on the difficulty of terrain,
                                    communication and weather encountered by the Italians in
                                    northern Greece, now confines its reporting of the Greco-Italian
                                    war to the publication of the text of Italian war communiqués.
                                    Reports of the actual extent of Italian reverses are not
                                    published in such a way as to make them clearly discernible to
                                    the German public.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>